item.description:
Get-TimeStamp function returns a time stamp in string format.
The output is either an ISO 8601 format 2020-11-05T15:49:14Z useful for logs or standard yyyyMMddHHmmss 20201105154912 for either logs or output files.
powershell Get-TimeStamp function Get-TimeStamp { param ( # Return an UTC ISO 8601 timestamp (ie: &#34;2020-06-16T17:33:27Z&#34;) [switch] $iso8601 = $false ) $String = switch ($iso8601.IsPresent) { true { &#39;yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ&#39; } false { &#39;yyyyMMddHHmmss&#39; } } (Get-Date).ToUniversalTime().ToString($String) }

